what is class?
A. A class is a user defined blueprint or prototype from which objects are created.  It represents the set of properties
or methods that are common to all objects of one type

What is object?
A. is an instance of the Class that has state and behavior.

What is the entry point of an application?
A. The main method is the entry point.

Why main is static?
A. It is static because keyword static allows main to be called without creating an object of the class.

Which class is the superclass of all classes?
A. Object Class

What is difference between path and classpath variables?
A.  PATH is an environment variable which is used to locate JDK binaries like "java" or "javac" command used to run java
program and compile java source file. CLASSPATH is an environment variable that is used by System or Application
ClassLoader to locate and load compile Java byte codes stored in the .class file.

What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
A. Interface is like contract. It cannot be instantiated. It has methods but they are not implemented. Interface gets
implemented in another class.
Abstract class, methods get implemented. Abstract class get extended. Cannot be instantiated.

Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
A. You cannot make an object from Interface class. Interface can get implemented into a new class, and you can create an
object from there.
or Abstract class.


what is Access Specifier?
A. Java access modifier specifies which classes can access a given class and its fields, constructors and methods.
Access modifiers can be specified separately for a class, its constructors, fields and methods.

What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
A. Object Oriented Programming is a way of writing computer programs using the idea of "objects" to represent data and methods.
 Inheritance: this is when a class has access to the members of its parent without having to be reimplemented.
 polymorphism: this is when a class can change the methods of its parents class to fit its specific needs as well as add its own members
 encapsulation: this is when we restrict the scope of certain members so that they cannot be manipulated outside of the class where they
 are defined, this is achieved with the "private keyword";
 abstraction: abstraction is the process of implementation hiding. we use it when we want certain features to be implemented.


What is Java Package and which package is imported by default?
A. a package is simply a folder or directory that stores related files and applications for easy access and readability
   The default package is an unnamed package. The unnamed package contains java classes whose source files did not contain a package declaration.

